CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, May 4, 1957, pg. 23 reads: " The Holloways - Mrs. Wilbert (Twyla) Holloway was a happy mother last Sunday when she walked proudly to church with son, Robert, one of Uncle Sam's Navy boys. Roger has just returned from a tour of the Mediterranean, and from here goes to Norfolk Naval Base. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Robert Holloway, standing between, possibly father Wilbert Holloway, and mother Twyla Holloway, standing across from Wesley Center AME Zion Church
